   OHP, France

   Lacoste, A.M., S. Godin, et G. Mégie, Lidar measurements and Umkehr
   observations of the ozone vertical distribution at the Observatoire de
   Haute-Provence, J. Atmos. Terr. Phys., 54, 571-582, 1992.

   McGee, T., P. Newman, M. Gross, U. Singh, S. Godin, S. Lacoste, et G.
   Megie, Correlation of ozone loss with the presence of volcanic
   aerosols, Geophys. Res. Lett., 21, 801-2.801, 1994.

   Guirlet, M., P. Keckhut, S. Godin and G. Mégie, Description of the
   long-term ozone data series obtained from different instrumental
   techniques at a single location: The Observatoire de Haute-Provence
   (43.9 °N, 5.7°E), Ann. Geophys., 2000.

   Braathen G.O., T.J. McGee, M.R. Gross, S. Godin, P. Keckhut, C. Vialle,
   and A. Hauchecorne, Intercomparaison of stratospheric ozone and
   temperature measurements at the Observatoire de Haute Provence during
   an NDSC validation campaign from 1-18 july 1997, To be submitted to
   Geophys. Res. Lett., 2000.

   Hohenpeißenberg, Germany

   Claude, H. and Steinbrecht, W. Long term ozone DIAL measurements at
   Hohenpeißenberg, intercomparisons with Brewer/Mast ozone sondes, HALOE,
   SBUV, and SAGE II, Advances in Atmospheric Remote Sensing with Lidar,
   Springer New York-Berlin-Heidelberg, 537-540, 1996.

   Steinbrecht, W.; Claude, H. and Schoenenborn, F. Nine years of lidar
   measurements at Hohenpeißenberg: Validation and results, Proc. Quadr.
   Ozone Symp. 1996, L'Aquila, Italy, (R. Boikov, G. Visconti, eds.),
   171-174; 1998.

   DDU, Antarctica

   Bergeret, V., S. Bekki, S. Godin and G. Mégie, Analyse des variations
   saisonnières de l'ozone antarctique dans la basse stratosphère à partir
   des données lidar et sonde de Dumont d'Urville, C.R. Acad. Sci. Sér. II
   a, 326, 751-756, 1998.

2. Temperature validation

   OHP, France

   Singh, U.N., P. Keckhut, T.J. McGee, M.R. Gross, A. Hauchecorne,
   E.F. Fishbein, J.W. Waters, J.C. Gille, A.E. Roche and J.M. Russell
